  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.13.2-stable\r\nCL client & version: prysm v4.0.8\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash :\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nOptions specified in config should enable metrics collection.\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[Metrics]\r\nEnabled = true\r\nEnabledExpensive = true\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThese options are ignored. Metrics server starts on 6060 port, but metrics are all zeroes, unless `--metric`s CLI arg is specified.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nAdd this lines to config.toml\r\n```toml\r\n[Metrics]\r\nEnabled = true\r\nEnabledExpensive = true\r\nHTTP = \"0.0.0.0\"\r\nPort = 6060\r\n```\r\n\r\nStart geth with flags `--pprof --pprof.port=6060 --pprof.addr=0.0.0.0`\r\n\r\nGo to `/debug/metrics/prometheus` endpoint and all metrics will be zeroes.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````",
